<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9969> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9969" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Privernatibus. MRR I.144, Itgenshorst no. 71, Rich no. 71." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/861> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #861" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.21.2; Fast. Cap. (rei gerundae causa), Degrassi 36f., 109, 418f.; attacked Saticula and defeated a force of Samnites (Liv. 9.21; cf. Diod. 19.65.7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/803> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #803" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The fourteenth in the series (Liv. 8.23.17)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/791> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #791" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.20.3; Chr. 354 (Privernas II et Declao); Fast. Hyd. (Mamertino II et Deciano), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 108, 412f. The Consuls reduced Privernum to surrender, celebrated triumphs, and moved to give the town favorable terms and citizenship (Liv. 8.20-21; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 541; Val. Max. 6.2.1; cf. Dio fr. 35.11). On Plautius, see Lübker no. 5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/790> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #790" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Denarii of P. Plautius Hypsaeus bear the inscriptions, C. Hupsae. cos. Priver. captu., and C. Ypsae. cos. Priv. cepit (Grueber 1.476f.; 2.589f.). The cognomen Hypsaeus however does not appear in the consular lists until 125 B.C. (See Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.150f.) Plautius' cognomen (his name is preserved entire in Act. Tr.) distinguishes him from the Consul of 341 and the Censor of 312 (Degrassi 108, 541)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/766> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #766" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "To hold elections (Liv. 8.16.12). See Degrassi 107, 410f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/765> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #765" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Aemilius, see Act. Tr. on 329; on that of Publilius, ib. on 339 and 315." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/731> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #731" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.1.1; Diod. 16.84.1; Chr. 354 (Venno II et Mamerco); Fast. Hyd. (Venoce II et Mamertino), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 107, 408f. Plautius held command against Privernum and the Volscians, Aemilius against the Samnites, who sent envoys to treat for peace (Liv. 8.1). On Plautius, see Lübker no. 18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/730> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #730" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Plautius, see 347, note 1. In Livy Aemilius is called T. Aemilius Mamercus, but Cassiod. and Diod. have Lucius. Fast. Hyd. and Chr. Pasc. indicate that the cognomen was probably Mamercinus in Fast. Cap. See Act. Tr. on 329. Plautius' command against Privernum may be referred to in coins of C. Plautius Hypsaeus (Grueber, CRRBM 1.476, and 485; 2.589), but see Degrassi 541, on 329." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/727> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #727" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.39.17 (Mamercus), cf. 42.3. See Degrassi 106, 408f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/726> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #726" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The identification is not completely certain. On the name of Aemilius, see Act. Tr. on 329." .
